[[Mary Berry (food writer)|Mary Berry]] is a British food writer, best known for her work with [[AGA cooker|AGA cooking]] and for baking. ''The Hamlyn All Colour Cookbook'' was her first published [[cook book]], in which she collaborated with Ann Body and Audrey Ellis. She has since gone on to write over seventy cook books,<ref name=allrise>{{cite news|last=Foster|first=Jill|title=All rise for Mary queen of cakes! Great British Bake Off judge shares a few slices of her wisdom|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/femail/article-2046689/Great-British-Bake-Off-judge-Mary-Berry-shares-wisdom.html|accessdate=31 March 2012|newspaper=The Daily Mail|date=8 October 2011}}</ref> which have sold over five million copies.<ref name=quadrille>{{cite web|title=Mary Berry|url=http://www.quadrille.co.uk/author/mary-berry/56|publisher=Quadrille Publishing|accessdate=31 March 2012}}</ref>
